The South African Reserve Bank (SARB) has welcomed the reappointment of Kuben Naidoo as one of the three Deputy Governors of the SARB for a second five-year term. Naidoo, whose reappointment is effective from April 1, to March 31, 2025, was first appointed a Deputy Governor on April 1, 2015. He has also been reappointed CEO of the Prudential Authority, effective April 1.